[b]Volume Strata[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Draws a fixed-range volume profile anchored to the right edge of your lookback window. Instead of floating to the left of the range, the profile grows leftward into the candle area — so the bars sit on top of the actual price action they represent. You see where volume clustered, which levels are dominant, how buy and sell pressure distributed across the range, and a rich set of contextual metrics about the profile shape and structure.

[b]Key features[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Right-anchored bars[/b] — up-volume is shown on the inner (right) side of each row, down-volume extends further left. The split is determined per candle using body/wick weighting, not a simple close-above-open rule.
[*][b]Blue / yellow split[/b] — buy volume in blue, sell volume in yellow (volume profile convention).
[*][b]Value area highlight[/b] — the configurable value area (default 70%) is shaded distinctly. Rows outside the area use lighter tones so the structure reads at a glance.
[*][b]Point of Control (POC)[/b] — dashed line at the highest-volume row, with a floating price label to the right. Color and width are configurable.
[*][b]VAH / VAL lines[/b] — dotted boundaries at the top and bottom of the value area, each with a price label. Toggle independently.
[*][b]Value Area fill[/b] — light shaded zone between VAH and VAL across the lookback range; the "fair value" band visualized at a glance.
[*][b]HVN zones[/b] — horizontal shaded bands at high-volume rows (mean + 1σ) extended across the lookback. The strongest reaction zones.
[*][b]LVN zones[/b] — horizontal shaded bands at low-volume local minima (below mean − 1σ). Price tends to move quickly through these — useful for breakout zones.
[*][b]Naked POC tracking[/b] — previous POCs that haven't been retested are drawn as faint dashed lines extending right. They are removed automatically once price touches them. Tracks new naked POCs from script load forward.
[*][b]Expanded info table[/b] — levels, VA width, range, POC strength, up-vol %, total volume, profile shape (D/P/b/B), VA state, Virgin POC, developing POC, POC distance in ATR.
[*][b]Alerts[/b] — POC cross, VA entry/exit, VAH/VAL touch.
[/list]

[b]How to read it[/b]
[list]
[*]Wide rows = high acceptance — price spent time and attracted volume here; expect support/resistance on revisits.
[*]Thin rows (especially between HVNs) = low-volume nodes — price tends to move quickly through these.
[*]HVN markers (gold) = the strongest magnetic levels in the range.
[*]LVN markers (cyan) = potential breakout zones; price rarely lingers here.
[*]Up-volume wider than down on a row = more buying pressure at that level. Down-volume wider = more selling.
[*]Profile shape gives a directional bias: P-shape (POC up high) = accumulation, b-shape (POC low) = distribution, D-shape = balanced, B-shape = transition.
[/list]

[b]Info table fields[/b]
[list]
[*][b]POC / VAH / VAL[/b] — key levels in the profile
[*][b]VA Width[/b] — value area as % of range. Compact (< 30%) suggests range trading; wide (> 60%) suggests trending or distributed activity
[*][b]Range[/b] — high − low of the lookback
[*][b]POC Str[/b] — % of total volume concentrated at the POC. High = strong reference; low = volume spread across many rows
[*][b]Up Vol[/b] — buy volume %. Green > 55%, red < 45%
[*][b]Total Vol[/b] — total volume in the lookback (K/M/B formatted)
[*][b]Shape[/b] — D (balanced), P (accumulation), b (distribution), B (double distribution)
[*][b]VA State[/b] — Inside / Above / Below value area
[*][b]POC[/b] — Virgin (untouched in last 5 bars) or Touched
[*][b]Dev POC[/b] — POC direction vs. previous bar
[*][b]POC Dist[/b] — distance of close from POC in ATR multiples
[/list]

[b]Settings[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Lookback Bars[/b] — how many bars the range covers (1–500)
[*][b]Rows[/b] — number of price buckets (5–100); more rows = finer granularity
[*][b]Value Area %[/b] — percentage of total volume defining the value area (classic: 70%)
[*]All lines, colors, and toggles are grouped under Colors and Display in the inputs panel
[/list]

